[{"playerName":"Wander Franco","RPM":"","Vel":"","cBonus":null,"cRisk":"","cETA":"","cFV":"50","cWeight":"160","cHeight":"5' 10\"","cRank":"1","cOVR":"","cORG":"","cDraftSchool":"Dominican Republic","Hit":"25 / 55","Game":"20 / 55","Raw":"45 / 55","Spd":"50 / 40","Fld":"40 / 45","Arm":"50 / 55","FB":"","SL":"","CB":"","CH":"","SPL":"","CT":"","CMD":"","cSeason":"2017","ID":3773,"RowID":1,"FirstName":"Wander","LastName":"Franco","Position":"SS","Age":"16.4","Team":"","Season":2017,"Type":"2017 July 2","PlayerId":"","DraftRank":1,"ProjTeam":"TBR","Ovr_Rank":0,"Org_Rank":0,"FV_Current":50,"Risk_Current":0,"ETA_Current":0,"Draft":"","CollegeCommit":"","Height":70,"Weight":160,"Bats":"S","Throws":"R","School":"Dominican Republic","Summary":"While many scouts expect Franco, who has a boxy frame which is carrying more mass than a typical J2 teenager, to make a range-based move off of shortstop at some point, he has such sticky hands and quick actions that he should be able to stay there for a while. Though his left-handed swing has a beer league softball vibe, Franco has innate feel for generating airborn contact and can spray it to all fields. He's more fluid and comfortable as a right-handed hitter and makes similarly strong contact. He has a chance to hit and hit for power while either playing short or playing plus or better defense at second or third.","YouTube":"","pHit":25,"fHit":55,"pGame":20,"fGame":55,"pRaw":45,"fRaw":55,"pSpd":50,"fSpd":40,"pFld":40,"fFld":45,"pArm":50,"fArm":55,"pFB":0,"fFB":0,"pSL":0,"fSL":0,"pCB":0,"fCB":0,"pCH":0,"fCH":0,"pSPL":0,"fSPL":0,"pCT":0,"fCT":0,"pCMD":0,"fCMD":0,"bRPM":0,"fRPM":0,"Range":"","Touch":0,"Variance":null,"State":null,"BirthDate":null,"TLDR":null,"Athleticism":null,"Frame":null,"Performer":null,"Delivery":null,"Agent":null,"ProjBonus":null,"Prev_Ovr_Rank":null,"Prev_Org_Rank":null,"Trend":null,"TJDate":null},{"playerName":"Daniel Flores","RPM":"","Vel":"","cBonus":null,"cRisk":"","cETA":"","cFV":"50","cWeight":"182","cHei